1.title: Hydra Attacks: Part 1
1.plot: Doctor octopus forms a New sinister six

2.title: Hydra Attacks: Part 2
2.plot: After being saved by Scarlet Spider following Arnim Zola's takeover of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Tri-Carrier, Spider-Man must work with him to liberate Manhattan and his fellow students from HYDRA's clutches. Even when they save Agent Venom and Iron Spider, they must also undo transformations of the HYDRA Goblins, avoid Doctor Octopus and Kraven the Hunter, and defeat Arnim Zola.

3.title: Miles from Home
3.plot: After learning that Norman Osborn injected himself with an Anti-Goblin serum to prevent further transformations into Green Goblin following the last encounter, Doctor Octopus teams up with Baron Mordo and uses the Siege Perilous to pull the Ultimate Green Goblin from Miles Morales' universe into theirs so that HYDRA can be his master. Now Spider-Man and Miles have to work together with Doctor Strange to keep the demonic Goblin from using the Siege Perilous to destroy reality.

4.title: Iron Vulture
4.plot: With the Siege Perilous destroyed in the aftermath of the fight with the Ultimate Green Goblin, Miles Morales is forced to stay in Spider-Man's reality until S.H.I.E.L.D. can find a way to get him and his world's Goblin back to their home, and Spider-Man works to keep him safe. After Norman Osborn becomes Iron Patriot, Spider-Man must help him when he is targeted by Doctor Octopus and Vulture.

5.title: Lizards
5.plot: After Spider-Man and the Web Warriors are told by Vulture that there is a spy among the other heroes, he and the Web Warriors work to find out who it is while Nova and Nick Fury are away on a secret mission. They test out the new training area that was designed by Leo Fitz and Jemma Simmons, only to discover that the robots were sabotaged. Dr. Connors once again becomes Lizard and now sports a contagious bite that turns others into lizards. When everyone ends up infected, it's up to Spider-Man to stop the Lizard and cure everyone before the infection spreads out of ...

6.title: Double Agent Venom
6.plot: Spider-Man and Scarlet Spider must overcome Kraven in order to rescue their kidnapped teammate, Agent Venom.

7.title: Beached
7.plot: As Spider-Man and Iron Spider pursue Vulture, their pursuit brings them to a nearby island where they discovered that Doctor Octopus has captured Sandman and has cloned him from his sand samples in order to find the "Ultimate Sandman" that would join his Sinister Six.

8.title: Anti-Venom
8.plot: Spider-Man and Agent Venom have been cracking down at defeating possible Sinister Six recruits like Shocker, Grizzly, and Beetle. When Doctor Octopus (now paired up with Dr. Michael Morbius) has made an entirely new symbiotic that's corrosive to the original one, it takes control of Harry Osborn after he and and his team intervenes. The Anti-Venom symbiotic controls Harry into destroying Spider-Man and Agent Venom as the new Anti-Venom. Now Spider-Man and Agent Venom must work with Iron Patriot to free Harry from the Anti-Venom symbiotic.

9.title: Force of Nature
9.plot: While answering a distress signal that leads them to an abandoned mall in Queens during a drought, Spider-Man, Kid Arachnid, Iron Spider, and Scarlet Spider find a vacuum-sealed room where they unknowingly release Hydro-Man. When Hydro-Man causes the Spider-Jet to do an emergency landing in a Queens neighborhood where Aunt May is, the Web Warriors must find a way to defeat Hydro-Man as Scarlet Spider works to keep Aunt May out of harm's way.

10.title: The New Sinister 6: Part 1
10.plot: After defeating Shriek, Spider-Man joins Flash Thompson, Amadeus Cho, Miles Morales, and Ben Reilly for Aunt May's birthday party. Things get worse when Doctor Octopus completes his Sinister Six upon assembling Kraven the Hunter, Ultimate Green Goblin, Rhino, Hydro-Man, and Electro where they attack the Triskelion. Even when most of the Sinister Six is defeated by the S.H.I.E.L.D. Academy students, Spider-Man is caught off guard when it turns out that there is a seventh member of Doctor Octopus' group that Spider-Man least suspects.

11.title: The New Sinister 6: Part 2
11.plot: Now that Doctor Octopus knows Peter Parker's identity and revealed how he had taken in Scarlet Spider following the defeat of Kraven the Hunter, Ultimate Green Goblin, Rhino, and Electro, he prepares for his next plan of action which involved getting the key to Dr. Curt Connors' latest invention. As Spider-Man works to keep Aunt May safe, he also enlists Sandman to deal with Hydro-Man.

12.title: Agent Web
12.plot: When a battered Nova ask for help finding Nick Fury, Spider-Man tracks into the dangerous ruins of an ancient city.

13.title: The Symbiote Saga: Part 1
13.plot: Michael Morbius steals a sample of the Venom symbiote off of Agent Venom as Crossbones orders him and a restrained Doctor Octopus to experiment with it. As Spider-Man and Agent Venom work to reclaim the Venom sample, the experiment enables the revival of the Carnage symbiote. Doctor Octopus uses a serum with vampire bat DNA in it to transforms Morbius into a white humanoid vampire bat as Doctor Octopus is infected by Carnage.

14.title: The Symbiote Saga: Part 2
14.plot: Carnage has been spread out the city and some of the superheroes Captain America, Luke, Iron fist, etc are trying to stop carnage. While Harry Osborn comes back as the anti-venom.

15.title: The Symbiote Saga: Part 3
15.plot: After the carnage was destroyed.Spider-man,Patriot and Agent venom were heading to clean up the city but unfortunately carnage returns and makes a way to mid town high where MJ is.Now its upto Peter,Harry and Flash to stop it from getting near MJ,while Morbius is trying to find "queen".

16.title: Return to the Spider-Verse: Part 1
16.plot: Spider-Man and Kid Arachnid head to alternate dimensions to collect the other pieces of the Siege Perilous, before unknown dangers can unfold.

17.title: Return to the Spider-Verse: Part 2
17.plot: Spider-Man and Kid Arachnid head to a Wild West Timeline, to find a piece from the Siege Perilous, where they run into Sherrif Doc Oc, who will stop at nothing to put them behind bars.

18.title: Return to the Spider-Verse: Part 3
18.plot: Spider-Man and Kid Arachnid travel into the Noir Timeline, in the hunt for the Siege Perilous, where they need to team up with Spider-Man Noir, and gangster Hulk, known as Fixit, in order to take down a new bad guy in control of a piece of the Siege Perilous, Mr Negative.

19.title: Return to the Spider-Verse: Part 4
19.plot: Spider-Man and Kid Arachnid are still in pursuit of the Siege Perilous shards. This time they wind up in Kid Arachnids Universe, where they run into a new spider who took up the mantel, Spider-Gwen. They need to find the shards before the "Wolf Spider" manages to get his hands on them.

20.title: Strange Little Halloween
20.plot: It's Halloween, and Spider-Man is in for a treat. All the trick-or-treating kids have been turned into the real life versions of their costumes, and it's up to Spider-Man, Ant-Man and Doctor Strange to turn the city back to normal.

21.title: The Spider Slayers: Part 1
21.plot: After getting caught off guard by an artificial Spider-Man look alike, Spider-Man teams up with an unlikely ally, in order to get to the bottom of who is trying to create an army of Spider-Men

22.title: The Spider Slayers: Part 2
22.plot: Spider-Man, Doc Oc, and Scarlet Spider travel to the sunken hydra heli-carrier in search of Scarlet Spiders past

23.title: The Spider Slayers: Part 3
23.plot: The Web Warriors and the Spider Slayers join forces to flush out a traitor on the tri-carrier who is attacking some of the other heroes, and destroying equipment.

24.title: The Moon Knight Before Christmas
24.plot: While house sitting for Dr. Strange on Christmas Eve, Spidey teams with the mysterious Moon Knight to confront his own Ghost of Christmas Past.

25.title: Graduation Day: Part 1
25.plot: Doctor Octopus threatens to harm Aunt May if Spidey ever puts on his mask again. Spider-Man must track down Doc Ock before he has a chance to put his plan into action..

26.title: Graduation Day: Part 2
26.plot: Peter Parker must find a way to stop Doctor Octopus and the Superior Sinister Six from destroying all of the heroes in New York and taking over the world.

1.title: Great Power
1.plot: One year after becoming Spider-Man, a teenage Peter Parker is approached by Nick Fury to train with SHIELD.

2.title: Great Responsibility
2.plot: When Spider-Man accepts Nick Fury's offer to be trained by SHIELD to become the Ultimate Spider-Man, he discovers that he will be joining forces with four other teenage Super Heroes: Nova, White Tiger, Power Man and Iron Fist.

3.title: Doomed
3.plot: Spider-Man and his team arrive in Latveria to track down the menacing Doctor Doom. However, things turn for the worst when Doctor Doom tricks the team into taking him aboard the Helicarrier.

4.title: Venom
4.plot: Doctor Octopus' newest creation Venom, an unstable clone derived from a blood sample from Spider-Man, shows up at Harry Osborn's house party and attacks Spider-Man and the other trainees, jumping from host to host.

5.title: Flight of the Iron Spider
5.plot: When Spider-Man meets his idol Iron Man, he receives a specialized gift: the Iron Spider suit. However, Spider-Man experiences difficulty learning how to use the suit and begins to neglect his teammates. Meanwhile, the heroes battle the Living Laser, who takes advantage of Spider-Man's lack of experience using the new suit.

6.title: Why I Hate the Gym
6.plot: Taskmaster goes undercover and infiltrates Peter's school to seek out Spider-Man. Spider-Man and White Tiger must put their differences aside and find a way to defeat an opponent who can mimic all of their physical abilities.

7.title: Exclusive
7.plot: Spider-Man agrees to a video interview with budding news reporter Mary Jane Watson, who gets a more exclusive scoop than she could ever have anticipated when Spider-Man and The Incredible Hulk engage in an all-out battle against Zzzax throughout Manhattan.

8.title: Back in Black
8.plot: It's bad enough when Peter catches a cold, but things go from bad to worse when a new Spider-Man dressed in black attempts to replace him.

9.title: Field Trip
9.plot: While on a field trip, Spider-Man and his superhero friends encounter the mighty Thor, who is transformed into a frog by his mischievous half-brother Loki. Now, the heroes must venture to the magical world of Asgard in order to save the nine realms from Loki's wrath.

10.title: Freaky
10.plot: After Spider-Man and the X-Man Wolverine apprehend the mutant Mesmero, the vengeful super villain uses his mental powers to switch their personalities, creating a serious identity problem for the two so different heroes.

11.title: Venomous
11.plot: Spider-Man is confronted with the dilemma when Venom once again resurfaces. Caught between either trying to save Harry on his own or putting his trust in his teammates, who are under orders to finish Venom for good.

12.title: Me Time
12.plot: After a fight with Whirlwind, Spider-Man insists on a weekend off from Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D.. Unfortunately, Doctor Octopus chooses this very time to attack Spider-Man when his job is threatened by Norman Osborn.

13.title: Strange
13.plot: When New York is plunged into a mystical sleep, Iron Fist and Spider-Man (who is at first highly sceptical of magic) seek the help of Doctor Strange. In order to break the spell, the three heroes must face their own worst fears in the face of the spell's initiator, the extradimensional entity known as Nightmare.

14.title: Awesome
14.plot: Spidey and Power Man fight the Juggernaut.

15.title: For Your Eye Only
15.plot: After being late for training, Spider-Man is faced against an evil super army called Zodiac and their leader, Scorpio, who took over the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier and set it on self-destruct. Spider-Man and Fury must put their differences aside and fight the new menace as a team.

16.title: Beetle Mania
16.plot: Spider-Man and his team are put on S.H.I.E.L.D. security detail to protect the all-too-critical-for-his-own-health J. Jonah Jameson from the Beetle, a prospect Spider-Man does not enjoy. Things do get personal when Spider-Man must also protect a highly determined Mary Jane, who is on her way to the Bugle for a job interview, from the high-tech villain.

17.title: Snow Day
17.plot: When Phil Coulson wants the heroes to report to the S.H.I.E.L.D. ice base for winter survival training, Spider-Man and his team sneak off for a vacation on a deserted tropical island that Nova found on the S.H.I.E.L.D. database. However, they soon realize that there is an inhabitant on the island who sees them as his new playmates... and does not want them to leave again.

18.title: Damage
18.plot: When Spider-Man and his fellow teenage super heroes cause too much damage in a fight with the Wrecking Crew, Nick Fury assigns them to work with the super clean-up company Damage Control. But while working with Damage Control, Spider-Man uncovers a villainous mystery.

19.title: Home Sick Hulk
19.plot: Hulk smashes back into Spider-Man's life where he is sick with an alien infection caused by the Phalanx. Fearing that S.H.I.E.L.D. would want to lock the Hulk away rather than help him, Spider-Man sees no choice but to take Hulk home and keep him hidden from Aunt May while protecting him from the Phalanx and Fury.

20.title: Run Pig Run
20.plot: Loki gets revenge on Spider-Man by turning him into a pig using an enchanted hot dog. Now, with the help of Thor and the entire S.H.I.E.L.D. force, "Peter Porker" must survive an Asgardian boar hunt across New York City.

21.title: I Am Spider-Man
21.plot: Peter Parker is shocked to discover that Midtown High is putting on a Spider-Man musical starring Flash Thompson as Spider-Man. Things only get worse when Trapster mistakes Flash for the real Spider-Man.

22.title: The Iron Octopus
22.plot: When Doctor Octopus takes over Iron Man's armors, Spider-Man works with Iron Man to stop his attacks on Oscorp and S.H.I.E.L.D.

23.title: Not a Toy
23.plot: Spider-Man loses Captain America's shield, and it ends up in the hands of Doctor Doom.

24.title: Attack of the Beetle
24.plot: To Peter's horror and jealousy, Aunt May and Coulson have become close and decide to go on a dinner date. Peter's intentions on crashing the party, however, are turned into a very literal crashing by the Beetle, who has an old grudge on Coulson.

25.title: Revealed
25.plot: Doc Ock and Norman Osborn's plans collide, leading to the creation of a dangerous new foe: The Green Goblin.

26.title: Rise of the Goblin
26.plot: Spider-Man and his team protect Harry Osborn from the Green Goblin, but even S.H.I.E.L.D. can't help them when the Goblin teams up with Venom.

1.title: The Lizard
1.plot: The Ultimate Spider-Man returns to stop a nefarious plot of Doctor Octopus.

2.title: Electro
2.plot: Spider-Man's old enemy Electro takes control of the city's electricity.

3.title: The Rhino
3.plot: Spider-Man must stop the Rhino's vendetta against Flash Thompson.

4.title: Kraven the Hunter
4.plot: White Tiger come to terms with her powers and origin.

5.title: Hawkeye
5.plot: Spider-Man and Hawkeye are forced to team up to fight The Beetle.

6.title: Sinister Six
6.plot: Can Spider-Man survive when he is trapped?

7.title: Spidah-Man
7.plot: Boston invites Spider-Man to become their official hero.

8.title: Carnage
8.plot: The Green Goblin plans to turn Spider-Man into his perfect weapon.

9.title: House Arrest
9.plot: SHIELD has to fight for their lives in Aunt May's house.

10.title: The Man-Wolf
10.plot: Spider-Man and his team travel to the moon.

11.title: Swarm
11.plot: A lab experiment at Stark Industries goes wrong.

12.title: Itsy Bitsy Spider-Man
12.plot: Spider-Man and his team are turned into mini-versions of themselves.

13.title: Journey of the Iron Fist
13.plot: Spider-Man travels to the mystical city of K'un L'un to help Iron Fist fulfull his destiny.

14.title: The Incredible Spider-Hulk
14.plot: The Hulk and Spider-Man switch minds, leading to lots of craziness!

15.title: Stan by Me
15.plot: Spider-Man goes on a hunt for The Lizard beneath Midtown High.

17.title: Venom Bomb
17.plot: Spidey must work with his nemesis, Doc Ock.

18.title: Guardians of the Galaxy
18.plot: Nova and Spider-Man team up with The Guardians of the Galaxy.

19.title: The Parent Trap
19.plot: Power Man and Spider-Man infiltrate Zodiac's secret volcano base.

20.title: Game Over
20.plot: Spider-Man teams up with Captain America and Wolverine to stop a threat.

21.title: Blade
21.plot: Spider-Man fights alongside vampire hunter Blade to stop Dracula.

22.title: The Howling Commandos
22.plot: With Spider-man's friends under the control of Dracula, Spidey teams up with The Howling Commandos.

23.title: Second Chance Hero
23.plot: Spider-Man forms an unlikely partnership with a cured Norman Osborn.

24.title: Sandman Returns
24.plot: Spider-Man tries to help The Sandman reform.

25.title: Return of the Sinister Six
25.plot: Spider-Man and his team are tested by a surprise attack from Doc Oc's reformed Sinister Six.

26.title: Ultimate
26.plot: Spider-Man fights against his own team to save all of New York from being turned into Green Goblins.

1.title: The Avenging Spider-Man: Part 1
1.plot: Loki joins forces with Doctor Octopus to destroy the Avengers and their newest member, Spider-Man.

2.title: The Avenging Spider-Man: Part 2
2.plot: After a case of mistaken identity, Spider-Man must convince his old team that he's the real Spider-Man before he is destroyed by his new team, The Avengers.

3.title: Agent Venom
3.plot: While trying to become a crime fighter, Flash Thompson gets permanently bonded with Venom, and it's up to Spidey to rescue his one-time school bully and help him.

4.title: Cloak and Dagger
4.plot: Spidey wants to recruit Cloak and Dagger as New Warriors for his S.H.I.E.L.D. team.

5.title: The Next Iron Spider
5.plot: Science genius Amadeus Cho proves perfect to operate the Iron Spider armor. The only trouble is he's Peter Parker's class rival. Can they work together?

6.title: The Vulture
6.plot: A mysterious thief known as The Vulture has been causing trouble. Spider-Man decides to track him down, and discovers he's a young man who has trouble remembering his past.

7.title: The Savage Spider-Man
7.plot: Spider-Man travels to the Land with Wolverine to find Ka-Zar. Things become complicated as a result of a plan hatched by Taskmaster and Kraven the Hunter.

8.title: New Warriors
8.plot: Spider-Man realizes he has inspired a whole new generation of aspiring super-heroes and wants to encourage them to have S.H.I.E.L.D. training and form a new team, the New Warriors.

9.title: The Spider-Verse: Part 1
9.plot: Goblin uses Electro to power up the siege perilous to collect the DNA of other Spider-Men. Spider-Man follows Goblin and boosts the confidence of Spider-Man 2099 and helps Spider-Girl to defeat Norma Osborn.

10.title: The Spider-Verse: Part 2
10.plot: Spider-Man continues following Green Goblin across the multiverse to stop him from collecting Spider-Men DNA. He helps Spider-Man Noir to renew his friendship with Mary Jane.

11.title: The Spider-Verse: Part 3
11.plot: Spider-Man helps Spyder-Knight take down the medieval Dr. Octopus and save York, then helps Miles Morales forgive himself for what happened to Peter Parker in his universe.

12.title: The Spider-Verse: Part 4
12.plot: Spider-Man finally ends up back in his own universe, he finds Green Goblin has injected himself with the Spider-Men DNA from all the universes to become the Spider-Goblin. With Electro's help from the Siege Perilous he summons all the Spider-Men dubbed Web-Warriors to battle the Spider-Goblin and save New York.

13.title: The Return of the Guardians of the Galaxy
13.plot: The Guardians of the Galaxy land on Earth to repair their ship at the same time Titus leads the Chitauri into targeting Nova's helmet. Now Spider-Man and Nova must work with the Guardians of the Galaxy to defeat Titus and the Chitauri.

14.title: SHIELD Academy
14.plot: Spider-Man's education at the Academy begins, but it might be cut seriously short when a long-dormant villain wakes from hibernation and sets out to destroy S.H.I.E.L.D.

15.title: Rampaging Rhino
15.plot: Spidey and Hulk are the last line of defense when a bitter rivalry between Agent Venom and Rhino threatens to destroy New York City.

16.title: Ant-Man
16.plot: Spider-Man and Ant-Man must shrink down to miniature size in a special submarine to rid Nick Fury's body of nanobots implanted by Doc Ock.

17.title: Burrito Run
17.plot: Craving Mexican food Spider-Man, Power Man and Squirrel Girl sneak out after hours for late-night burritos. Along the way they must contend with some of Spidey's enemies.

18.title: Inhumanity
18.plot: Spider-Man is the only one prepared to support Triton of the Inhumans as he returns to his home city to stop his people attacking and save New York from a war between S.H.I.E.L.D. and the Inhumans.

19.title: Attack of the Synthezoids
19.plot: Spidey's fellow superheroes have been replaced by synthetic replicants by the evil Dr. Zola. Who can Spidey trust to help save the S.H.I.E.L.D. Academy?

20.title: The Revenge of Arnim Zola
20.plot: While freeing classmates Spider-Man is captured by Arnim Zola and absorbed into his body. The freed friends must fight Zola to help Spider-Man escape the madman.

21.title: Halloween Night at the Museum
21.plot: It's up to Spider-Man and the cast of JESSIE to save Halloween from Morgan Le Fey and her plans to plunge Earth into eternal night!

22.title: Nightmare on Christmas
22.plot: Spider-Man sees what the world would be like without him when Nightmare takes the web-slinger on a journey through his past, present and future.

23.title: Contest of the Champions: Part 1
23.plot: In this first of a four part story, Spider-Man, the Avengers and the Agents of S.M.A.S.H. battle their greatest foes for the fate of the planet. In the first round Spider-Man is chosen to be part of The Collector's team and is partnered with Hulk and Iron Man against The Grandmaster's team of villains consisting of Kraven, Molten Man and The Wendigo King.

24.title: Contest of the Champions: Part 2
24.plot: In this second of a four-part story, Spider-Man, the Avengers and the Agents of S.M.A.S.H. battle their greatest foes for the fate of the planet. Spider-Man is partnered with Captain America, Red Hulk and Iron Fist in a game of capture the flag against Sandman, Blastaar and Ymir. Then Spider-Man is partnered with Power Man, Black Widow and Skaar against Doctor Octopus, Absorbing Man and Zzzax in a game of last team standing but things become a problem when the Grandmaster starts changing the environment of the game.

25.title: Contest of the Champions: Part 3
25.plot: In this third of a four-part story, Spider-Man, the Avengers and the Agents of S.M.A.S.H. battle their greatest foes for the fate of the planet. Spider-Man teams up with Iron Spider, Agent Venom and Thor against Terrax, Attuma and Annihilus. Then Spider-Man uses LMDs to distract The Grandmaster so he, Iron Spider and Agent Venom can board Grandmasters ship to save the hostages. Can his plan succeed?

26.title: Contest of the Champions: Part 4
26.plot: In this final part of a four-part story, Spider-Man, the Avengers and the Agents of S.M.A.S.H. battle their greatest foes for the fate of the planet. The Grandmaster has won the Contest of Champions, but Spidey asks for a winner take all rematch, can Spider-Man win?

imdb.plot outline: It's been a year, and Spider-Man is still finding the superhero life is full of dangerous pitfalls and avoidable collateral damage. Fortunately, Nick Fury, Director of S.H.I.E.L.D., offers to fix that with a special training program that offers to make Peter Parker the Ultimate Spider-man. Now the quintessential superhero loner must learn to get along with a new team of superheroes as fellow students, both in his professional and personal life. Between those demands and the supervillains, life is as hectic as ever for the Webslinging Wonder.
imdb.title: Ultimate Spider-Man
plot: While being trained by S.H.I.E.L.D., Spider-Man battles evil with a new team of teen colleagues.::Kenneth Chisholm

synopsis: Ultimate Spider-Man will be a unique journey exploring our favorite web-slinger as he teams up with other fan favorite Marvel Super Heroes in never before seen stories with a new life filled with great challenges, new friends, intense action and character growth. Ultimate Spider-Man will tell a coming of age story, where hapless Peter Parker evolves from a naive teen hotshot to a true hero who comes to terms with his origins and abilities. As the storyline begins, Peter Parker has been Spider-Man for just one year. Hes fought villains, saved lives, but still has much to learn about being a super-hero. Now, Nick Fury gives Peter the chance to go to the next level to train to be a real super-hero and become The Ultimate Spider-Man. But before he can do that, Peter will have to learn how to work with a team of fellow teenage super-heroes. Along the way, he will have to navigate challenging relationships with mentors and super-colleagues, and emerge with a better understanding of his parents' legacy and his own destiny.
